  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison writes that his baby, Eilizabeth Pease Garrison, died this morning from lung fever. Garrison says: &quot;No strange thing has happened unto us, in view of human mortality---nothing dark or mysterious; yet we feel our bereavement deeply and tenderly.&quot; They would like to have Theodore Parker present at the funeral tomorrow afternoon and &quot;to express whatever sentiments the occasion may suggest.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The letter is signed: Wm. Lloyd and Helen E. Garrison.</subfield>
  </datafield>
